    {
        "content": "<p>I think that you cannot define and use an attribute in the same file: the file where the attribute is used should <em>import</em> the file where the attribute is registered.</p>\n<p>If you move</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">@[</span><span class=\"n\">rom</span><span class=\"kd\">]</span> <span class=\"c1\">-- unknown attribute rom</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">def</span> <span class=\"n\">womp</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"bp\">+</span> <span class=\"mi\">2</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">4</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>to a separate file importing the previous one, it should work.</p>",
